 Remove RTF artifacts throughout text
 Fix repetitive phrases:

"Jeff clutched the Codex tightly" (appears 8+ times)
"The Codex grew warm in his hands" (appears 6+ times)
"Jeff's mind reeled" (appears 5+ times)


 Standardize character names (Sylphus vs Viridessa inconsistency)
 Clean up excessive italics in opening chapters

üü° IMPORTANT - Story Improvements
Pacing Adjustments

 Slow down the opening

Add 1-2 more chapters in Mayfield showing Jeff's dissatisfaction
Show him trying and failing to find meaning before the yard sale
Build more connection to what he's leaving behind


 Add breathing room between major events

Insert quieter character moments between battles
Show Jeff processing his transformation more gradually


 Restructure the middle section

Chapters 15-18 jump too quickly between major events
Add transitional scenes showing the Conclave's daily operations



Character Development

 Deepen Jeff's internal conflict

Add scenes where he misses his old life
Show him struggling with the responsibility
Include moments of doubt and failure


 Develop Alexis Void earlier

Introduce hints of their presence before Chapter 4
Add a backstory reveal chapter
Make their philosophy more nuanced than "unmake everything"


 Give secondary characters more distinct voices

Pyx needs consistent speech patterns beyond just being mischievous
Myriad should have a unique philosophy/worldview
Add personal stakes for Guardian Conclave members



World-Building Clarification

 Create a glossary of terms (Codex, Veiled Realms, Primordial Word, etc.)
 Add a map or realm diagram as front matter
 Establish clearer rules for:

How the Codex actually works
Limits of reality manipulation
Cost/consequences of world-jumping



