Were they once like Jeff? What broke them?


The cost of power (throughout)

Physical toll on Jeff's body
Losing touch with humanity
Memory confusion from multiple realities



Plot Strengthening

 Add foreshadowing for the Architect earlier in the story
 Create a "darkest hour" moment where Jeff genuinely considers giving up
 Establish a ticking clock - why must the threat be stopped NOW?
 Add a betrayal subplot - someone in the Conclave working against them
 Include consequences for Jeff's choices - people/worlds lost

Relationship Development

 Add a mentor figure who dies/disappears midway through
 Develop Jeff/Alexis dynamic - make them dark mirrors of each other
 Create a connection to Mayfield - someone there who notices Jeff is gone
 Build found family dynamics within the Guardian Conclave

